237. Davus, a common slave's name, said to be from Arios, a Dacian, the older name of this tribe having been Δοῖοι, according to Strabo vn. 304. The name occurs in the Andria of Terence; -Forcellini and the dictionaries based on Freund say also in Plautus, but this is an error: no characterio Plautus bears the name3 it occurs only in Amphitr. 361 as a jest.
